A multi-objective mixed-integer non-linear programming (MINLP) model is developed to minimize both the total

constraint for a secure border patrol. A solution algorithm is proposed to achieve the Pareto-optimal set. This
method provides the decision-maker with a set of candidate solutions to choose from based on their priorities and

budgetary constraints. We illustrate our method using a case study on a segment of the US-Mexico borderline.
